siteDescrip: Managed field with half mowed every other year to promote lowbush blueberry (Vacciniumspp.). Two-year-old side is dominated by blueberry in peak flower and grasses. Few other plants in bloom in meadow and bees were only seen using the blueberry. Bumble bees were all queens. Based on four counts of 50 bees randomly sampled they were as follows: ternarius (90.5%), perplexus (4.0%), terricola (2.0%), vagans/sandersoni (these should be definit4ely ID'ed by malar space etc.; 1.5%), borealis (1.0%), impatiens (0.5%), bimaculatus (0.5%).Ê
collectionNotes: might have been collecting pollen but didn't hear any buzzing

Based on four counts of 50 bees randomly sampled they were as follows: ternarius (90.5%), perplexus (4.0%), terricola (2.0%), vagans/sandersoni (these should be definit4ely ID'ed by malar space etc.; 1.5%), borealis (1.0%), impatiens (0.5%), bimaculatus (0.5%).Ê
collectionNotes: might have been collecting pollen but didn't hear any buzzing
